article_title: Scott Walker's Replacement For The ACA Would Leave Many Uninsured

article_metadata.author: Business in the Beltway

og.description: GOP presidential hopeful Scott Walker’s plan to replace the Affordable Care Act is built on a controversial framework of tax subsidies that Walker estimates would cost about $1 trillion over 10 years. The plan is already drawing heat from fellow GOP candidate Bobby Jindal, who called it “a new entitlement program” [...]
